Hey there, 
I would like to know why in the Geth code got sometimes the Past EIPs with some `if` statements? 
I mean, is this possible that the nodes aren't running the same version but still sync together? 
(I suppose) Probably, with some *light* EIP (like only renaming OPInstruction etc should be working as this is not a breaking changes?). 
But in the case of **London** for example: 
Inside the code I can see this:

```golang
    var userRefund uint64
    if !rules.IsLondon {
        // Before EIP-3529: refunds were capped to gasUsed / 2
        userRefund = st.refundGas(params.RefundQuotient)
    } else {
        // After EIP-3529: refunds are capped to gasUsed / 5
        userRefund = st.refundGas(params.RefundQuotientEIP3529)
    }

```
I would like to know the reason why we keep previous EIPs here (3529)? 
The following statement shouldn't be entering in this one right? (or this possible with old nodes somehow?)
```
        // Before EIP-3529: refunds were capped to gasUsed / 2
```
Maybe there is compatibility things I am probably missing here? if you got some example would be glad to hear more about it!
